      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., mean absolute error, normalized RMSE) computed between predicted and measured hemolysis index values across all validation operating points, with metric value documented and compared against acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index values were compared against bench measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error of 8.3% was computed. However, the comparison was performed using a single-operator visual inspection protocol without a pre-specified quantitative acceptance threshold documented prior to the study; the 15% tolerance cited was established post-hoc after reviewing the data. No formal uncertainty propagation from experimental measurement error into the comparison metric was carried out. As a result the output comparison activity satisfies only the documentation requirements of Gradation 1 rather than the pre-specified threshold requirement of Gradation 2 mandated at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
