      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest (relative hemolysis index, shear-stress distribution) directly relevant to the COU decision on worst-case hemolysis operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH derived from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model applied to Lagrangian particle tracks. This quantity directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged shear stress and exposure time distributions. All QoIs are directly relevant to the COU. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
